PROCLAMATION NO. 1932

CREATING AND DESIGNATING SEVERAL PARCELS OF LAND OF THE PUBLIC DOMAIN SITUATED WITHIN THE CAPITOL COMPLEX IN CADLAN, PILI AND MAYCATMON, MILAOR, CAMARINES SUR, AS TOURISM ECONOMIC ZONE PURSUANT TO REPUBLIC ACT NO. 7916 AS AMENDED BY REPUBLIC ACT NO. 8748

Pursuant to the powers vested in me under Republic Act No. 7916, otherwise known as the Special Economic Zone Act of 1995 as amended by Republic Act No. 8748 (an Act amending Republic Act 7916, otherwise known as the “Special Economic Zone Act of 1995”) and upon the recommendation of the Board of Directors of the Philippine Economic Zone Authority, I, GLORIA MACAPAGAL-ARROYO, President of the Philippines, do hereby create and designate, subject to the provisions of Republic Act No. 7916 as amended, its Implementing Rules and Regulations, Resolution No. 02-342 dated 10 October 2002 and Resolution No. 07-468 dated 10 October 2007, of the Board of Directors of the Philippine Economic Zone Authority, several parcels of land situated within Capitol Complex in Cadlan, Pili and Maycatmon, Milaor, Camarines Sur, as Tourism Economic Zone to be known as Camarines Sur Tourism Park with an aggregate area of Seven Hundred Thirty Thousand Nine Hundred Twenty Seven (730,927) Square Meters, more or less, as defined by the following technical description:

